title: The Story of the Lancaster
description:
As RAF Bomber Command took the war to the enemy under Air Marshall Arthur Harris, the four-engined Avro Lancaster reigned supreme, replacing the rugged, reliable Wellington in laying waste to German cities by night. 

This most successful of all World War II &#039;heavies&#039; could carry more than it&#039;s own weight in bomb load, including the 22,000 pound Tallboy - the biggest conventional weapon ever made. And when fearless Guy Gibson led 617 Squadron to fame on the low-level Dambuster raid - one of the war&#039;s most daring operations - the Lancaster was confirmed as an aviation Legend. 

With recent colour film of &#039;City of Lincoln&#039;, the RAF&#039;s last airworthy Lancaster, among the wartime footage, this is the Lancaster&#039;s dramatic story.
